<section>
	<h1>About the App</h1>
	<p>
		<strong>Buy Later</strong> helps prevent impulse purchases in today's modern online shopping environment.
	</p>
	<p>
		Have you ever spontaneously bought something and then a few days later realized you didn't actually want or need it?
	</p>
	<p>
		It can be easy to open an app and buy something in under a minute. <strong>Buy Later</strong> is designed to
		create a buffer in that moment. The app provides a minimal, clean interface where you can list things you want
		as you think of them — once they make it through the fixed hold period, you can buy them (if you still think
		it's a good idea).
	</p>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Features</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Minimalist user interface</li>
		<li>Fixed 10, 20, or 30 day hold period</li>
		<li>Notifications when an item's timer completes (optional)</li>
		<li>Always free: 100% ad-free, no sign-in, no subscriptions</li>
		<li>Private: all data lives on your device — nothing is ever transmitted or retained</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>System Requirements</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>iOS 14.0 or later</li>
		<li>iPhone and iPad optimized</li>
		<li>Offline-only: all data stays on your device</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
	<dl>
		<dt>How do I add a new item?</dt>
		<dd>Tap the <strong>+</strong> button on the Pending tab, enter your item, and hit Save. Your timer starts immediately.</dd>

		<dt>How do I delete an item?</dt>
		<dd>Swipe left on the item you want to delete.</dd>

		<dt>Where can I see completed items?</dt>
		<dd>Switch to the <em>Completed</em> tab to review all items whose countdown has finished.</dd>

		<dt>Can I customize the timer length?</dt>
		<dd>Yes — you can choose a 10, 20, or 30 day hold period in Settings.</dd>

		<dt>Where is my data stored?</dt>
		<dd>
			All data is stored locally on your device and is not accessible anywhere else. If you delete the app, all data is lost.
			<a href="privacy">View our privacy policy.</a>
		</dd>
	</dl>
</section>

